description:
&lt;p&gt;University College London Hospital Staff Bank is currently Band 2 Pharmacy Technicians to join the Staffbank. Full-time opportunities available, Monday to Friday&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role will be to assist the department in various duties such as dispensary, outpatient reception, stock management and ward rounds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pharmacy experience in a hospital/community environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be working towards or hold a NVQ L2 in pharmacy services or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 Months NHS experience working as a Pharmacy Assistant Required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to use own initiative and follow all departmental standard operating procedures at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working for UCLH Bank will provide you with an array of benefits;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First opportunity for work placements before agency staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to work across the trust in different departments gaining invaluable experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay rates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated booking consultant available to assist with any queries and advise on suitable assignments, tailored to you&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electronic timesheet system with weekly payroll&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are seeking an opportunity to further develop your skills as a Assistant Technical Officer and are interested in joining this great team then please apply directly. One of our recruitment team will contact you shortly.&lt;/p&gt;
